    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>DVD discs on which data can be stored and which is designed to be used as read-only memory. These have been used to distribute software applications that exceed the capacity of a CD-ROM disc. DVD-ROM discs are read in DVD-ROM and DVD-RAM drives in computers, but typically not in DVD drives connected to TVs and home theater systems.</Note_Text>
